1
00:02:24,841 --> 00:02:27,636
I'm alone, and I want
to keep it that way.

2
00:02:27,707 --> 00:02:30,298
I lost my wife and son.

3
00:02:30,373 --> 00:02:34,135
- Well, ask the bartender.
He can find anything.
- No.

4
00:02:34,207 --> 00:02:36,002
They're dead.

5
00:02:38,841 --> 00:02:41,398
Do you wanna talk about it?

6
00:03:10,673 --> 00:03:12,798
Any guys here
taking this Viagra? Let's see.

7
00:03:12,873 --> 00:03:14,930
Not one honest guy.

8
00:03:15,005 --> 00:03:17,733
Have you--
Okay?

9
00:03:17,806 --> 00:03:21,568
You know, you have to be--
A friend of mine dropped one of
these Viagra pills on the floor...

10
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:24,366
and his dog swallowed it.

11
00:03:24,439 --> 00:03:26,962
Now he has a pointer. Anyway--

12
00:03:29,406 --> 00:03:32,998
- We have to talk about this.
- I know. You're right.

13
00:03:35,773 --> 00:03:38,001
But do you really think
we can save this marriage...

14
00:03:38,073 --> 00:03:41,061
now that I've decided I like Leno
better than Letterman?

15
00:03:41,139 --> 00:03:44,469
Don't. I'm sorry.

16
00:03:44,539 --> 00:03:47,471
I remember when my jokes
used to make you laugh.

17
00:03:47,539 --> 00:03:49,471
They do. I just--

18
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:58,628
- We have to talk about this.
- There's nothing to talk about.

19
00:03:58,705 --> 00:04:01,763
Oh, of course there is.

20
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,771
But I don't want to.

21
00:04:07,306 --> 00:04:09,238
Okay.

22
00:04:12,206 --> 00:04:14,138
What about the party?

23
00:04:14,206 --> 00:04:16,798
Well, nothing's changed.
I have a brain tumor...

24
00:04:16,872 --> 00:04:19,599
but I'm going to that party,
with or without you.

25
00:04:19,673 --> 00:04:22,195
We've put a deposit down.

26
00:04:24,005 --> 00:04:25,937
Mission accomplished.

27
00:04:29,472 --> 00:04:30,530
I am in love.

28
00:04:31,272 --> 00:04:32,760
In love?

29
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:34,771
Yes, in love.

30
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:38,271
But before we go further,
let me say this.

31
00:04:38,339 --> 00:04:42,031
Before we go...
further--

32
00:04:42,105 --> 00:04:46,469
I can't go any further.

33
00:04:46,538 --> 00:04:50,300
It's almost 1:00, Meredith. 1:00.

34
00:04:50,371 --> 00:04:54,304
- And I got a day job, remember?
- Yeah. Phil needs his sleep.
He's a postal worker.

35
00:04:54,371 --> 00:04:56,564
All right, slackers.
Trot off home.

36
00:04:57,638 --> 00:04:59,933
Good night.

37
00:05:00,005 --> 00:05:02,868
- Settle a bet I have with Phillip?
- Yeah.

38
00:05:02,939 --> 00:05:06,132
He claims you have
no personal life whatsoever.

39
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:08,331
I say that's impossible.

40
00:05:08,405 --> 00:05:10,997
I hope it wasn't a large bet.

41
00:05:11,071 --> 00:05:13,969
On equity waiver salary
you can't afford to lose much.

42
00:05:14,038 --> 00:05:15,971
No Mr. Right?

43
00:05:17,105 --> 00:05:19,535
Ms. Right?

44
00:05:19,605 --> 00:05:23,196
No inclination for either at the moment.
Thank you very much.

45
00:05:23,271 --> 00:05:26,964
But if you're fishing,
"mister" is my gender of choice.

46
00:05:27,038 --> 00:05:30,436
You're a wonderful person.
You should have someone in your life.

47
00:05:30,505 --> 00:05:32,436
That's all I'm saying.

48
00:05:32,505 --> 00:05:37,164
I can still be a wonderful person
and not have anybody in my life.

49
00:05:37,238 --> 00:05:40,227
Look, I'm just not interested
in a relationship right now.

50
00:05:40,305 --> 00:05:42,237
You are such a liar.

51
00:05:43,704 --> 00:05:46,499
I am such a liar.

52
00:05:55,472 --> 00:05:58,063
Front desk.

53
00:05:58,138 --> 00:06:00,070
Hold that, please!

54
00:06:04,504 --> 00:06:08,903
Did she not say,
"Hold that, please"?
Or isn't English your first language?

55
00:06:22,337 --> 00:06:24,270
Any trouble getting away?

56
00:06:24,337 --> 00:06:26,565
He has his acting class tonight.

57
00:06:26,638 --> 00:06:30,296
- You want me to get champagne?
- I don't think I have time for that.

58
00:06:32,171 --> 00:06:35,227
In case you're planning on
being gentle tonight...

59
00:06:36,238 --> 00:06:38,067
don't be.

60
00:07:23,570 --> 00:07:25,503
Mom?

61
00:07:27,736 --> 00:07:30,258
Welcome to Chicago.

62
00:07:32,004 --> 00:07:35,231
You look awful.

63
00:07:35,304 --> 00:07:39,100
- You should get some sleep.
- I'll sleep when you sleep.

64
00:07:47,303 --> 00:07:49,463
It happened three days ago.

65
00:07:49,537 --> 00:07:53,764
The last time I talked with her--
my wife Leann--

66
00:07:54,937 --> 00:07:57,062
It was about 3:00.

67
00:07:57,137 --> 00:08:01,126
She was taking our son Jamey
to, uh, soccer practice.

68
00:08:03,470 --> 00:08:07,835
Uh, I had a meeting at a bar.

69
00:08:07,903 --> 00:08:12,232
I'd had a few drinks. No more
than usual-- standard four-drink buzz.

70
00:08:12,303 --> 00:08:14,235
Maybe five.

71
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:20,800
After, I was gonna meet Leann and Jamey
at the Pizza Hut.

72
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:25,127
Every Tuesday night
Jamey wants Pizza Hut.

73
00:08:26,869 --> 00:08:29,267
So I was late.

74
00:08:29,336 --> 00:08:31,734
I was driving fast.

75
00:08:31,803 --> 00:08:35,428
Not too fast, I think.

76
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:39,902
The light, it just turned.

77
00:08:41,869 --> 00:08:43,802
It was red for only a second.

78
00:08:43,869 --> 00:08:45,892
Less than.
I swear.

79
00:08:48,503 --> 00:08:50,435
I ran the light.

80
00:08:53,369 --> 00:08:55,494
I saw the car.

81
00:08:55,569 --> 00:08:58,195
I hit my wife's car.

82
00:08:58,269 --> 00:09:00,201
Oh, my God.

83
00:09:00,269 --> 00:09:04,201
I saw her face through the windshield
just as I hit them.

84
00:09:06,702 --> 00:09:09,691
She saw me.

85
00:09:09,769 --> 00:09:12,429
She knew it was me.

86
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,567
Oh.

87
00:09:16,903 --> 00:09:18,925
You shouldn't be alone.

88
00:09:20,303 --> 00:09:22,326
Yes, I should.

89
00:09:22,403 --> 00:09:24,891
I should be alone in hell.

90
00:09:24,969 --> 00:09:26,902
That's where I am.

91
00:09:59,669 --> 00:10:04,125
Twenty minutes at 350 degrees
is absolutely essential.

92
00:10:04,202 --> 00:10:06,225
No more, no less.

93
00:10:06,302 --> 00:10:09,928
And the delicacy of this fish
is best appreciated by its taste...

94
00:10:10,001 --> 00:10:13,229
not necessarily by its appearance.

95
00:10:13,302 --> 00:10:15,325
Once you remove the fish
from the oven...

96
00:10:17,335 --> 00:10:20,596
transfer it directly
onto a heated plate.

97
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:31,831
There's one thing that's
paramount for every cook to keep
in the back of their mind.

98
00:10:38,368 --> 00:10:40,596
Only you know
what goes on in the kitchen.

99
00:10:40,669 --> 00:10:44,101
Hannah's Country Kitchen Cooking.

100
00:10:46,302 --> 00:10:48,234
And we're clear.

101
00:10:48,302 --> 00:10:52,791
Hannah, that was incredible!
I smell a fourth Emmy.

102
00:10:56,601 --> 00:10:58,965
I don't wanna see any more
of these. Hmm?

103
00:10:59,035 --> 00:11:01,296
Tough. Oh, l--

104
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:04,766
Mmm. It's delicious.
What?

105
00:11:04,835 --> 00:11:07,232
Nothing.

106
00:11:12,402 --> 00:11:14,890
You can never stop, can you?

107
00:11:14,968 --> 00:11:18,627
- Stop what?
- Organizing things.

108
00:11:18,701 --> 00:11:22,155
- Oh, I'll stop if it bothers you.
- No.

109
00:11:22,235 --> 00:11:25,224
It doesn't bother me.
It takes me back.

110
00:11:28,401 --> 00:11:30,663
Sit next to me.

111
00:11:42,001 --> 00:11:44,432
It's a hell of a way
for you to find out, huh?

112
00:11:44,501 --> 00:11:47,592
- Find out what?
- Well, that I'm gay, for one.

113
00:11:49,468 --> 00:11:51,957
Come on.
You never suspected?

114
00:11:52,034 --> 00:11:55,932
- You were always so good at sports.
- Mom!

115
00:11:56,001 --> 00:12:00,456
I'm really glad you're here.

116
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:05,263
- And what's the second thing?
- What second thing?

117
00:12:05,334 --> 00:12:09,595
You said it was a hell of a way
for me to find out that you
were gay for "one" thing.

118
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:12,099
- So what's the second thing?
- That I'm dying.

119
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:15,964
- Don't say that!
- Oh, stop! I can't go back into
our classic mother-son pattern.

120
00:12:16,034 --> 00:12:21,126
Okay? I can't play the Iverson family
game of denying reality...

121
00:12:21,201 --> 00:12:23,792
- where reality is over there,
somewhere...
- Oh, honey, don't.

122
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:27,163
and we hide from it over here
and pretend it doesn't exist.

123
00:12:27,234 --> 00:12:31,064
Okay? It takes too much energy.
Energy that I don't have.

124
00:12:31,134 --> 00:12:33,326
All right. Maybe I don't either...
have the energy.

125
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,389
God, that would be good.

126
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:37,933
All right, we'll start fresh.

127
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,932
Pattern-free.

128
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:44,160
Within these four walls,
reality will prevail.

129
00:12:44,233 --> 00:12:47,529
And if I slip up,
you-- you let me know.

130
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:49,498
You'll--
You'll be the first.

131
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,896
They say first steps
are the hardest.

132
00:13:02,933 --> 00:13:05,991
The doctor said
you haven't had any visitors.

133
00:13:06,067 --> 00:13:10,862
You know me, Mom. I've never been
one to have a lot of friends.

134
00:13:10,934 --> 00:13:14,923
Besides, I seem to be
the last of my small crowd.

135
00:13:14,999 --> 00:13:17,056
What about your roommate Jack?

136
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:23,594
He wasn't my roommate, Mother,
and he died a year ago.

137
00:13:28,467 --> 00:13:30,433
Hey, how's the commercial going?

138
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:32,432
It's on hold for a week.

139
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:37,057
The geniuses at Pacific Motors
have now decided to spotlight the car...

140
00:13:37,133 --> 00:13:39,065
and dumb down the concept.

141
00:13:39,133 --> 00:13:43,792
- No Fellini?
- Who? Most definitely no Fellini.

142
00:13:43,867 --> 00:13:46,526
But my play's not falling apart.

143
00:13:46,599 --> 00:13:48,623
- I'm happy for you.
- Thank you.

144
00:13:48,699 --> 00:13:50,790
Bosco, where do you keep
Theater Week?

145
00:13:50,866 --> 00:13:54,889
Top shelf. Between Psychology Today
and Martha Stewart Living.

146
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,531
Uh-oh!
Whoa!

147
00:13:59,599 --> 00:14:02,691
Jesus! Meredith?

148
00:14:02,766 --> 00:14:05,755
Jimmy, grab that side! Grab that side.
Okay. Everyone. All right, fellas.

149
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:09,425
On three. One--
Oh. Okay. All right.

150
00:14:09,499 --> 00:14:12,159
- Can we say "lawsuit"?
- Uh, are you okay?

151
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:15,256
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Fine.
I landed on a stack of George.

152
00:14:15,332 --> 00:14:18,424
- Plenty of padding.
- Meet the architect.

153
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:22,626
- Are you sure you're okay?
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine. Thank you.

154
00:14:22,699 --> 00:14:26,187
- If I can just find one,
Theater Week is on me.
- And dinner is on me.

155
00:14:26,265 --> 00:14:30,221
- No, no. Not necessary. Truly.
- Please. I insist.
It's the least I can do. I mean--

156
00:14:30,299 --> 00:14:33,663
- Look, I'm not gonna sue you, okay?
- I didn't think you were gonna sue me.

157
00:14:36,132 --> 00:14:38,894
Not that I couldn't, mind you.
But something tells me...

158
00:14:38,966 --> 00:14:42,228
that you'd be able to convince
the jury that this was my fault.

159
00:14:42,299 --> 00:14:47,096
You know I'm not just asking you
to dinner as a preemptive strike
against litigation.

160
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:49,654
- I'm asking because--
- I'll have dinner with you.

161
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:54,560
- What changed your mind?
- Anybody who can say
"preemptive strike...

162
00:14:54,632 --> 00:14:57,723
against litigation" with a straight face
deserves a dinner companion.

163
00:14:57,799 --> 00:15:00,629
Thank you.

164
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,321
This is last week's.

165
00:15:03,466 --> 00:15:07,160
I'm thinking of putting
the show on hiatus.

166
00:15:07,232 --> 00:15:09,824
And I'm thinking
you'll do no such thing.

167
00:15:09,898 --> 00:15:15,229
- But, Paul--
- No. I don't want anything
to be any different.

168
00:15:15,299 --> 00:15:19,026
- Things are different.
- I don't want to have a fight with you.

169
00:15:19,098 --> 00:15:22,292
I don't want a fight. I just--
I just want to talk and make--

170
00:15:22,365 --> 00:15:26,695
Look. What about what I want?
You've always controlled everything:

171
00:15:26,766 --> 00:15:28,755
your shows, the kids.

172
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,559
Stop trying to control me.

173
00:15:31,631 --> 00:15:33,620
I'm not trying
to control anybody.

174
00:15:33,698 --> 00:15:36,494
- I just think maybe--
- Don't think.

175
00:15:36,565 --> 00:15:40,361
Let us just proceed as if
nothing has changed. All right?

176
00:15:44,566 --> 00:15:48,622
- I don't know if I can do that.
- You have no choice.

177
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:53,794
I may have just enough time left
to become an alcoholic.

178
00:16:27,598 --> 00:16:31,190
I don't care who had her first. I poke
around her stool looking for worms.

179
00:16:31,265 --> 00:16:33,322
I feed the fucking thing.
I take her to the vet.

180
00:16:33,398 --> 00:16:35,523
All you do is pet her twice a day.

181
00:16:35,598 --> 00:16:38,496
Which is a hell of a lot more
than you've been doing to me lately.

182
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:40,723
Okay, let's discuss this calmly.

183
00:16:40,798 --> 00:16:44,560
We're adults.
We've been together a long time.

184
00:16:44,631 --> 00:16:46,994
Well, not a long time,
but an adequate four months.

185
00:16:47,065 --> 00:16:50,929
Adequate until you fuckin' cheated on me
with that skag from Bloomingdale's!

186
00:16:50,997 --> 00:16:52,930
You fu--
Harry?

187
00:16:52,998 --> 00:16:56,657
Don't you dare hang up.
Harry! Harry?

188
00:16:57,932 --> 00:17:00,420
Shit! Shit.

189
00:17:07,764 --> 00:17:10,356
Hi. You got a quarter?

190
00:17:14,965 --> 00:17:16,896
Thank you.

191
00:17:22,363 --> 00:17:24,296
The fucking cat is mine.

192
00:17:25,465 --> 00:17:28,260
No, no.
On this I'm not negotiable, Harry.

193
00:17:28,331 --> 00:17:31,263
Harry. Hey! Hey!
Don't be a fuckin' infant, okay?

194
00:17:31,331 --> 00:17:35,285
You can take anything that came
from IKEA. I want the cat,
and I want Pottery Barn.

195
00:17:35,364 --> 00:17:37,795
It--
One more time.

196
00:17:37,864 --> 00:17:40,763
You hang up one more time and l--

197
00:17:40,831 --> 00:17:42,763
Damn it.

198
00:17:46,363 --> 00:17:48,988
- It's my last one.
- Negotiations are almost over.

199
00:17:51,031 --> 00:17:52,963
Thank you.

200
00:17:57,197 --> 00:18:00,527
All right. Okay, scumbag.
You're robbing me blind...

201
00:18:00,597 --> 00:18:04,393
but I will give up Pottery Barn
if I can just have the cat.

202
00:18:05,897 --> 00:18:09,260
No! No. Pottery Barn does not
include Williams Sonoma.

203
00:18:09,330 --> 00:18:12,524
They're two separate
establishments, Harry.

204
00:18:12,597 --> 00:18:15,029
Oh, Christ on crutches!
Okay, you know what, Harry?

205
00:18:15,096 --> 00:18:19,052
I want to get rid of you as much as l
want to get rid of that junk from IKEA.

206
00:18:19,131 --> 00:18:21,562
So here's the thing.

207
00:18:21,630 --> 00:18:25,619
You can walk away with Pottery Barn,
Williams Sonoma, IKEA.

208
00:18:25,697 --> 00:18:30,561
And just to show you that I'm
a grown-up, I will throw in all
the crap from Hold Everything!

209
00:18:30,629 --> 00:18:33,425
Yeah! Yeah, that includes
the hanging shoe sorter.

210
00:18:33,497 --> 00:18:37,361
That's right.
Do we have a deal? Great.

211
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:40,521
So here's the thing.
I will be home in two hours.

212
00:18:40,596 --> 00:18:43,926
You and all your junk
from the catalogs will be gone...

213
00:18:43,996 --> 00:18:46,622
and the cat will be there waiting
for me, purring contentedly.

214
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:54,755
Well, the least I can do
after taking your last quarter
is let you buy me a drink.

215
00:19:07,596 --> 00:19:10,619
I work in the Twin Towers.
Entertainment law.

216
00:19:12,729 --> 00:19:15,127
- And you?
- Me?

217
00:19:15,196 --> 00:19:17,321
I'm not very good company.
I'm-- I'm sorry.

218
00:19:19,696 --> 00:19:21,628
No problem.

219
00:19:25,162 --> 00:19:28,288
- I'm not gonna bother you.
- Uh, don't go. l-l-I'm sorry.

220
00:19:28,362 --> 00:19:31,294
- No, I'm sorry. Really.
- Again, I'm sorry.

221
00:19:33,563 --> 00:19:36,858
- You've had a bad day.
- A killer.

222
00:19:36,930 --> 00:19:41,192
You know, yesterday I would have
said that things couldn't
possibly get any worse.

223
00:19:41,262 --> 00:19:43,694
They sure as hell
got worse today.

224
00:19:45,263 --> 00:19:49,093
I'm, uh--
I work in the, uh, Twin Towers too.

225
00:19:49,162 --> 00:19:52,651
I'm a development executive
over at ABC.

226
00:19:52,729 --> 00:19:56,491
I'm responsible for all those shit shows
that you don't watch on Thursday night.

227
00:19:56,563 --> 00:19:58,926
You're to blame for those?

228
00:19:58,996 --> 00:20:01,359
Afraid so.

229
00:20:01,429 --> 00:20:03,361
Everybody blames me.

230
00:20:03,429 --> 00:20:07,384
My boss, my wife, my secretary.

231
00:20:07,463 --> 00:20:09,395
Hell, even my kids.
They watch NBC.

232
00:20:09,463 --> 00:20:13,191
And I work like a dog...

233
00:20:13,262 --> 00:20:16,956
trying to find some way to fix
the Thursday night schedule.

234
00:20:20,862 --> 00:20:23,590
Well, I don't find a way to fix
the Thursday night schedule...

235
00:20:23,663 --> 00:20:25,788
and my boss,
today he tells me...

236
00:20:25,862 --> 00:20:29,760
that coming into the office
tomorrow isn't necessary.

