01:07:41,364 --> 01:07:43,853
I've already seen this one.
Alone.

957
01:07:43,930 --> 01:07:48,022
I was just wondering when you were
planning on speaking to me again.

958
01:07:48,097 --> 01:07:50,688
I mean, about something
other than Psycho.

959
01:07:50,763 --> 01:07:54,059
It's almost been 24 hours
since we traded barbs.

960
01:07:54,131 --> 01:07:57,927
We don't want to get rusty, do we?

961
01:07:57,997 --> 01:08:02,623
I mean, just how much longer
do I have to wait...

962
01:08:02,696 --> 01:08:04,719
for my next dose of vitriol?

963
01:08:04,797 --> 01:08:06,730
How long have you got?

964
01:08:06,797 --> 01:08:11,059
A good question.

965
01:08:15,197 --> 01:08:17,719
Oh, damn.

966
01:08:17,797 --> 01:08:21,286
On the first date
my husband asked me:

967
01:08:21,364 --> 01:08:25,456
"Gracie... do you dream?"

968
01:08:26,696 --> 01:08:29,288
And I said, "Yes."

969
01:08:29,363 --> 01:08:34,524
From the time I get up in the morning
until I go to bed at night.

970
01:08:34,596 --> 01:08:38,051
You know how they say
the first time is never any good?

971
01:08:39,696 --> 01:08:42,958
Well, with us, it was wonderful.

972
01:08:46,863 --> 01:08:49,795
I never felt so awake.

973
01:08:51,530 --> 01:08:56,121
I had to reassure him that crying
was just my standard reaction...

974
01:08:56,197 --> 01:08:58,627
to tremendous pleasure.

975
01:09:01,363 --> 01:09:05,295
He held me, and he said
that he wanted to make me cry...

976
01:09:05,363 --> 01:09:08,624
for the rest of our lives.

977
01:09:09,862 --> 01:09:12,294
Flash forward 15 years...

978
01:09:12,363 --> 01:09:17,625
and somehow the two of us
became one... and one.

979
01:09:20,463 --> 01:09:24,293
And now I find myself living with
a roommate instead of a husband.

980
01:09:24,363 --> 01:09:26,454
And I have dogs instead of children...

981
01:09:26,529 --> 01:09:29,963
because I can have dogs,
but I can't have children.

982
01:09:30,029 --> 01:09:32,961
And--

983
01:09:33,029 --> 01:09:37,155
Oh, I've forgotten
who blames who for that.

984
01:09:41,196 --> 01:09:43,628
And I haven't cried
in a very long time.

985
01:09:54,129 --> 01:09:59,221
My breaking point
happened this afternoon...

986
01:09:59,295 --> 01:10:02,693
when I picked up my kids
from day care.

987
01:10:04,796 --> 01:10:06,728
With you...

988
01:10:06,796 --> 01:10:10,728
I was spontaneous for the first time
in my entire life.

989
01:10:12,129 --> 01:10:15,151
And I discovered
I'm not very good at spontaneity.

990
01:10:17,463 --> 01:10:21,394
Is there something that you can see
your husband doing...

991
01:10:21,462 --> 01:10:24,054
or saying that would
make a difference?

992
01:10:24,129 --> 01:10:27,720
Sometimes I think it could be as simple
as his asking me to go for a walk.

993
01:10:27,796 --> 01:10:29,728
Um...

994
01:10:31,629 --> 01:10:34,891
anything, so long as it felt
like a start.

995
01:10:34,962 --> 01:10:37,394
Maybe this was your start.

996
01:10:37,462 --> 01:10:40,519
You're a fucking optimist.

997
01:10:40,595 --> 01:10:43,322
That's my job.

998
01:10:54,728 --> 01:10:58,820
This doesn't change anything
about Saturday, does it?

999
01:10:58,895 --> 01:11:02,828
This doesn't change anything
about Saturday.

1000
01:11:05,128 --> 01:11:09,027
So, let me take a stab
at Keenan's story.

1001
01:11:10,228 --> 01:11:12,160
You had a great love.

1002
01:11:12,228 --> 01:11:14,160
The romance of your lifetime.

1003
01:11:14,228 --> 01:11:17,456
Totally cosmic, out-of-this-world bond
with little Miss X...

1004
01:11:18,562 --> 01:11:20,493
and she left you.

1005
01:11:20,561 --> 01:11:23,153
You're not far off.

1006
01:11:23,228 --> 01:11:25,353
People get over these things, Keenan.

1007
01:11:25,429 --> 01:11:28,088
Hell, I'm getting over these things...
all the time.

1008
01:11:28,162 --> 01:11:30,321
Well, it can only be once for me.

1009
01:11:30,395 --> 01:11:33,259
You're sweet to believe things
so absolutely...

1010
01:11:33,328 --> 01:11:35,816
but you're also full of shit.

1011
01:11:36,961 --> 01:11:38,893
You can love again.

1012
01:11:38,961 --> 01:11:42,893
I can't.
Any more than you--

1013
01:11:42,961 --> 01:11:45,483
- Any more than I can what?
- I don't know.

1014
01:11:45,561 --> 01:11:47,618
A-Any more than you
can stop drinking.

1015
01:11:55,994 --> 01:11:57,984
- Can I get you another one?
- No, I'm fine. Thanks.

1016
01:11:58,060 --> 01:12:01,288
- It was a gin martini, right?
- Vodka, but, really, I've had enough.

1017
01:12:01,361 --> 01:12:04,089
- I insist, please.
- Look, pal--

1018
01:12:04,161 --> 01:12:07,287
And I mean this affectionately,
all right? Scram.

1019
01:12:08,995 --> 01:12:11,756
Where were we?
Oh, yes, I've just given up alcohol...

1020
01:12:11,827 --> 01:12:14,293
and you're going to tell me
about the great love of your life.

1021
01:12:14,362 --> 01:12:18,088
- Her name was Sarah.
- And she was your first?

1022
01:12:18,162 --> 01:12:20,093
Yes.

1023
01:12:20,161 --> 01:12:23,924
Look... it's natural
to elevate our first love...

1024
01:12:23,995 --> 01:12:27,085
to some sort of
mythic emotional plateau.

1025
01:12:27,161 --> 01:12:29,593
But you fell in love, she left you...

1026
01:12:29,660 --> 01:12:31,923
and now you're dealing with
love's most common byproduct:

1027
01:12:31,995 --> 01:12:33,961
suicidal manic depression.

1028
01:12:34,028 --> 01:12:35,822
Right?

1029
01:12:35,894 --> 01:12:39,088
- Do you feel better?
- No.

1030
01:12:40,995 --> 01:12:44,256
It-- It's hard to talk about.

1031
01:12:44,327 --> 01:12:47,157
I have a friend,
a jazz musician, trumpet player.

1032
01:12:47,227 --> 01:12:50,250
Really terrific.
I go and hear him jam every month or so.

1033
01:12:50,327 --> 01:12:53,521
an old Chet Baker song.

1034
01:12:53,594 --> 01:12:57,321
And he blows the same notes every time,
but every time it sounds different.

1035
01:12:57,394 --> 01:13:01,689
And we had drinks one night--
when I used to drink--

1036
01:13:01,760 --> 01:13:03,692
and I tried to tell him
how that song made me feel...

1037
01:13:03,760 --> 01:13:07,522
how his playing made me feel,
how the music... made me feel.

1038
01:13:07,593 --> 01:13:10,685
And he just kept shaking
his head and he said...

1039
01:13:10,760 --> 01:13:12,693
"Joan, you can't talk about music.

1040
01:13:12,760 --> 01:13:16,022
Talking about music is like
dancing about architecture."

1041
01:13:16,927 --> 01:13:18,859
I said, "Well, okay, fine.

1042
01:13:18,927 --> 01:13:21,586
Gonna get all philosophical on me.
It's as pointless as talking
about a lot of things.

1043
01:13:21,660 --> 01:13:23,592
Love, for instance."

1044
01:13:23,660 --> 01:13:26,183
And my friend laughed,
and he said...

1045
01:13:26,260 --> 01:13:28,193
"Definitely. Most definitely.

1046
01:13:28,261 --> 01:13:31,455
Talking about love is like
dancing about architecture."

1047
01:13:31,527 --> 01:13:33,856
So, I don't know.
He might be right.

1048
01:13:35,261 --> 01:13:38,420
But it ain't gonna
stop me from trying.

1049
01:13:40,627 --> 01:13:44,559
I wish you'd do that
- smile.

1050
01:13:44,627 --> 01:13:47,184
So do l.

1051
01:13:50,260 --> 01:13:53,783
So let me guess. You and Wonder Woman
were together a year?

1052
01:13:53,860 --> 01:13:56,451
A year and a half.

1053
01:13:56,527 --> 01:13:58,550
And you were faithful to her?

1054
01:13:58,627 --> 01:14:00,888
Completely.

1055
01:14:00,960 --> 01:14:03,687
And you shared everything.

1056
01:14:09,827 --> 01:14:13,657
We-- We shared everything.

1057
01:14:15,026 --> 01:14:17,117
That must be nice.

1058
01:14:18,527 --> 01:14:21,118
It was...

1059
01:14:21,193 --> 01:14:23,125
but...

1060
01:14:25,026 --> 01:14:29,789
in addition to sharing
all of those things...

1061
01:14:29,859 --> 01:14:33,951
it turns out I was also sharing her...

1062
01:14:34,026 --> 01:14:36,651
with a variety of other people.

1063
01:14:38,027 --> 01:14:39,958
I hate to say this...

1064
01:14:40,026 --> 01:14:42,584
because l-l don't want
to diminish your feelings...

1065
01:14:42,660 --> 01:14:46,284
but, sadly, that happens every day.

1066
01:14:46,360 --> 01:14:48,882
Those other people shared needles.

1067
01:14:56,793 --> 01:15:00,384
She died last year.

1068
01:15:02,958 --> 01:15:07,050
But not before sharing...

1069
01:15:07,125 --> 01:15:10,683
one final thing with me.

1070
01:15:58,893 --> 01:16:01,949
Can I buy you a drink, Valery?

1071
01:16:02,025 --> 01:16:04,753
You seem to be so good at this.

1072
01:16:04,825 --> 01:16:07,986
Oh, I'm fine in scene class,
on stage.

1073
01:16:08,058 --> 01:16:11,990
It's just this improvisational--
I can't do it.

1074
01:16:12,058 --> 01:16:13,990
- Hmm.
- At least not like this.

1075
01:16:15,391 --> 01:16:18,449
Maybe I'm just better
at pretending I'm someone else.

1076
01:16:20,391 --> 01:16:24,324
Well, I gotta go. Um... I'll see you
in class tomorrow for the reports.

1077
01:16:24,392 --> 01:16:26,983
God knows what I'll say.

1078
01:16:27,058 --> 01:16:30,649
- I won't be there.
- Why?

1079
01:16:30,725 --> 01:16:34,782
I, uh-- I like this too much.

1080
01:16:34,858 --> 01:16:38,984
- I'm too good at it.
- I don't understand.

1081
01:16:39,058 --> 01:16:42,490
I'm better at all these lies
that I've manufactured...

1082
01:16:42,559 --> 01:16:45,150
than I am at the lies I'm living.

1083
01:16:48,558 --> 01:16:51,183
I have a wife.
Did you know that?

1084
01:16:53,792 --> 01:16:56,087
I don't think that
we like each other very much.

1085
01:16:58,191 --> 01:17:00,714
Is that something
to smile about?

1086
01:17:03,158 --> 01:17:06,250
Well, it's just that my wife--
She, um...

1087
01:17:06,325 --> 01:17:09,313
doesn't think that I have
much of an imagination.

1088
01:17:09,391 --> 01:17:11,618
If she only knew.

1089
01:17:13,158 --> 01:17:15,920
If she only knew a lot of things.

1090
01:17:15,992 --> 01:17:18,718
If I only knew a lot of things.

1091
01:17:18,792 --> 01:17:20,723
Such as?

1092
01:17:22,658 --> 01:17:24,590
Where to start:

1093
01:17:24,658 --> 01:17:27,920
with myself...

1094
01:17:27,992 --> 01:17:31,151
with my wife.

1095
01:17:43,924 --> 01:17:46,913
They got it back.

1096
01:17:46,991 --> 01:17:49,719
They got what back?

1097
01:17:49,791 --> 01:17:51,724
The police. Your car.

1098
01:17:51,791 --> 01:17:55,189
Oh, right. Yeah.

1099
01:17:55,258 --> 01:17:57,190
Keenan, listen, I'm--

1100
01:17:57,258 --> 01:18:00,520
You don't have to say anything. l-l told
you because I wanted to tell you.

1101
01:18:02,757 --> 01:18:06,349
I wanted to because for
the first time in a long time
I wish things were different.

1102
01:18:06,425 --> 01:18:09,118
- They can be.
- No, they can't.

1103
01:18:17,258 --> 01:18:19,450
Well, none of this means
you can't love.

1104
01:18:19,525 --> 01:18:22,854
Joan, it means exactly that.
It doesn't mean anything else.

1105
01:18:22,924 --> 01:18:25,390
I don't believe that for a second,
that you can't love.

1106
01:18:25,458 --> 01:18:27,515
- I can't.
- Stop saying that.

1107
01:18:27,590 --> 01:18:31,522
It's the only thing I can say
to make you understand.

1108
01:18:33,123 --> 01:18:37,181
This may sound corny, but--

1109
01:18:37,257 --> 01:18:40,690
But you don't want me.

1110
01:18:40,757 --> 01:18:42,723
I-I'm damaged goods.

1111
01:18:42,790 --> 01:18:47,849
For Christ's sake,
we're all damaged goods.

1112
01:18:47,924 --> 01:18:51,856
I'm wandering around through life
with hardly any purpose or goal at all.

1113
01:18:51,923 --> 01:18:54,355
I don't know what
I'm doing half the time...

1114
01:18:54,424 --> 01:18:56,686
but I know that I can love.

1115
01:18:56,757 --> 01:18:59,018
I know that I can love you.
I know that I do love you.

1116
01:18:59,091 --> 01:19:02,284
- I won't let you love me.
- Why?

1117
01:19:04,924 --> 01:19:08,014
I won't let you love me because...

1118
01:19:12,590 --> 01:19:15,021
because I love you.

1119
01:19:16,823 --> 01:19:19,187
You love me?

1120
01:19:19,257 --> 01:19:21,246
- Can I go?
- No!

1121
01:19:23,323 --> 01:19:25,686
Do you know how long I have waited
for somebody I care about...

1122
01:19:25,757 --> 01:19:28,154
to say that they love me
and for me to actually believe them?

1123
01:19:28,223 --> 01:19:30,348
And if you think you're getting out
of this car, you're insane!

1124
01:19:30,424 --> 01:19:32,515
It will never work.

1125
01:19:33,923 --> 01:19:35,855
It's already working.

1126
01:19:35,923 --> 01:19:39,014
It's working.

1127
01:19:45,256 --> 01:19:47,654
I thought--
I thought you didn't cry.

1128
01:19:47,723 --> 01:19:49,848
I thought you didn't date.

1129
01:19:49,923 --> 01:19:53,787
Surprise, I'm crying...

1130
01:19:53,856 --> 01:19:55,947
and this is very much a date.

1131
01:19:56,023 --> 01:20:00,455
It's unconventional, perhaps,
but it's the best date I've ever had.

1132
01:20:09,356 --> 01:20:12,288
I can't!

1133
01:20:12,357 --> 01:20:16,448
No-- Keenan, please!
Please don't go!

1134
01:20:35,523 --> 01:20:37,455
Hey!

1135
01:20:37,523 --> 01:20:41,115
Hi, buddies.
How are you?

1136
01:20:41,189 --> 01:20:43,280
Who's a good boy?
Who's a good boy?

1137
01:20:50,189 --> 01:20:52,553
You're home early tonight.

1138
01:20:53,789 --> 01:20:56,051
You as well.

1139
01:20:56,123 --> 01:20:58,781
Well, inventory's almost over.

1140
01:20:58,855 --> 01:21:01,878
How is your improv class?

1141
01:21:01,956 --> 01:21:04,615
It finished tonight.

1142
01:21:04,688 --> 01:21:07,553
I thought you had
another couple days.

1143
01:21:07,622 --> 01:21:13,419
Well, I should say that
I finished tonight.

1144
01:21:13,488 --> 01:21:15,648
It wasn't what you had in mind?

1145
01:21:15,723 --> 01:21:17,654
Ultimately, no.

1146
01:21:17,722 --> 01:21:23,212
Well... I'm sure you'll find
something you enjoy.

1147
01:21:26,789 --> 01:21:28,721
I mean, to keep you occupied.

1148
01:21:30,155 --> 01:21:32,713
I'm going to try.

1149
01:21:42,622 --> 01:21:45,214
Well, as the British say,
I'm knackered.

1150
01:21:47,455 --> 01:21:50,320
You know what Saturday is, don't you?

1151
01:21:50,388 --> 01:21:52,321
I do.

1152
01:21:52,389 --> 01:21:54,820
Okay.

1153
01:21:54,889 --> 01:21:57,321
It might be easier if we meet there.

1154
01:21:57,388 --> 01:21:59,980
Whatever's easier.

1155
01:22:00,054 --> 01:22:03,817
All right. Did you feed the dogs?
You gave them their pills?

1156
01:22:03,888 --> 01:22:07,650
Okay. Well, don't forget to turn out
the light before you come to bed.

1157
01:22:07,722 --> 01:22:10,483
- I won't.
- Tomorrow's trash day.

1158
01:22:17,388 --> 01:22:21,717
There isn't much more
we can do, except ease the pain.

1159
01:22:22,822 --> 01:22:25,310
All right.

1160
01:22:25,388 --> 01:22:27,649
Ease the pain.

1161
01:22:41,387 --> 01:22:43,650
- Mom?
- Yes, honey.

1162
01:22:43,721 --> 01:22:45,711
- Mom?
- I'm here.

1163
01:22:45,788 --> 01:22:48,481
Wh-Where's Jack?

1164
01:22:48,555 --> 01:22:52,146
- He's not here.
- He was just here a minute ago.

1165
01:22:52,220 --> 01:22:55,119
- No?
- No.

1166
01:22:55,188 --> 01:22:59,416
- It was... you who were here.
- Yes, I'm here.

1167
01:22:59,488 --> 01:23:03,977
- You are here, aren't you?
- Yes, I'm here.

1168
01:23:06,488 --> 01:23:08,749
Tell me about death.

1169
01:23:25,654 --> 01:23:28,586
Remember a long time ago...

1170
01:23:28,654 --> 01:23:31,143
when you were still
inside my belly...

1171
01:23:31,220 --> 01:23:34,914
and the contractions began?

1172
01:23:36,988 --> 01:23:40,317
Well, they're beginning again.

1173
01:23:40,387 --> 01:23:44,251
- Read me that story.
- What story?

1174
01:23:44,321 --> 01:23:47,253
The one with the rabbit
and the rocking chair.

1175
01:23:50,654 --> 01:23:52,813
- Good Night, Moon?
- Yeah.

1176
01:23:52,887 --> 01:23:56,342
I like the ending.
Read me the ending.

1177
01:24:13,587 --> 01:24:17,178
Good night, comb.

1178
01:24:17,254 --> 01:24:20,481
Good night, brush.

1179
01:24:20,554 --> 01:24:23,020
Good night, nobody.

1180
01:24:25,587 --> 01:24:28,519
Good night, mush.

1181
01:24:31,421 --> 01:24:36,353
Good night to the old lady
whispering hush.

1182
01:24:38,420 --> 01:24:40,352
Good night, stars.

1183
01:24:42,087 --> 01:24:46,678
Good night... air.

1184
01:24:49,920 --> 01:24:53,283
Good night, noises...

1185
01:24:56,520 --> 01:24:58,453
everywhere.

1186
01:25:51,353 --> 01:25:56,217
Do you ever wonder if
while we spend all this time
anthropomorphizing our animals...

1187
01:25:56,285 --> 01:25:58,717
maybe they're just
anthropomorphizing us?

1188
01:25:58,787 --> 01:26:00,809
Hmm.

1189
01:26:00,887 --> 01:26:04,375
I didn't think so.
Who? Keenan?

1190
01:26:04,453 --> 01:26:08,215
No. Trust me,
I'll never hear from him again.

1191
01:26:08,285 --> 01:26:12,877
Well, I'm sorry to disappoint you,
but I'm fresh out of jokes.

1192
01:26:12,953 --> 01:26:16,385
What, is that a rhetorical question?
Why is my life so complicated?

1193
01:26:16,453 --> 01:26:20,215
Gee, I don't know.
Why is your life so fucking simple?

1194
01:26:20,286 --> 01:26:22,877
Hold on. There's someone at the door.

1195
01:26:22,952 --> 01:26:25,611
Well, I don't know until I answer it,
do l? Yeah, I'll ask who it is.

1196
01:26:25,685 --> 01:26:27,618
Hold on.
Yeah.

1197
01:26:31,886 --> 01:26:33,545
Hi.

1198
01:26:33,619 --> 01:26:35,710
Hi.

1199
01:26:35,786 --> 01:26:39,115
Um, I'm just on the phone.
I'm gonna wrap it up, okay?

1200
01:26:49,352 --> 01:26:51,285
M.C.I.

1201
01:26:51,353 --> 01:26:53,614
They're geniuses at tricking you
into conversation.

1202
01:26:53,685 --> 01:26:56,412
I can't stop thinking about you.

1203
01:26:56,485 --> 01:26:58,314
I love conversations that
start with the guy saying...

1204
01:26:58,386 --> 01:27:00,248
"l can't stop thinking about you."

1205
01:27:00,318 --> 01:27:02,944
Mind you, I've never actually
been on the receiving end
of any of those conversations.

1206
01:27:03,019 --> 01:27:04,950
Just looking at you
makes me happy.

1207
01:27:05,019 --> 01:27:07,144
I have--
I have to sit down.

1208
01:27:10,119 --> 01:27:14,483
When we're together,
whether or not I show it...

1209
01:27:14,551 --> 01:27:19,041
I just can't wait to hear
the next words out of your mouth.

1210
01:27:19,118 --> 01:27:23,244
But right now I need to ask you
to do something for me.

1211
01:27:23,318 --> 01:27:25,250
Anything.

1212
01:27:25,318 --> 01:27:28,977
Shut up.
Just for a moment.

1213
01:27:29,051 --> 01:27:31,779
I've been-- I've been thinking about
what you said last night.

1214
01:27:33,385 --> 01:27:37,147
I have no idea
why you're so relentless...

1215
01:27:37,218 --> 01:27:39,809
particularly, given the arsenal
of defenses I've thrown at you.

1216
01:27:39,885 --> 01:27:41,817
But...

1217
01:27:43,551 --> 01:27:49,450
no matter how hard I've tried to block
out everything that you've said...

1218
01:27:49,518 --> 01:27:51,541
the message has been received.

1219
01:27:54,985 --> 01:27:58,246
In a place inside me
that I thought had died.

1220
01:27:59,318 --> 01:28:02,045
But it hasn't.

1221
01:28:03,818 --> 01:28:07,580
And that place inside me
is alive and well.

1222
01:28:11,151 --> 01:28:13,242
I can't make any promises...

1223
01:28:13,318 --> 01:28:15,749
but...

1224
01:28:15,818 --> 01:28:18,579
I'd like to try and be with you.

1225
01:28:21,218 --> 01:28:25,240
It won't be easy,
but I'd like to try.

1226
01:28:25,317 --> 01:28:27,545
Can I say something?

1227
01:28:35,717 --> 01:28:39,411
You're right.
It won't be easy, but...

1228
01:28:42,484 --> 01:28:44,677
that's okay.

1229
01:28:46,151 --> 01:28:50,311
I want to be with you, but,
you have to understand, l, um--

1230
01:28:50,384 --> 01:28:52,407
- We can't--
- Have sex.

1231
01:28:52,484 --> 01:28:55,917
It may not be the conventional wisdom,
but it's the only way I can do this.

1232
01:28:55,984 --> 01:28:58,109
At least for the time being.

1233
01:28:59,483 --> 01:29:01,450
That's not a problem?

1234
01:29:01,517 --> 01:29:07,075
When was having sex
or not having sex not a problem?

1235
01:29:07,151 --> 01:29:11,913
To be honest, it's gonna
be difficult not to express
physically what I feel for you...

1236
01:29:11,984 --> 01:29:16,383
but...
we can look for other ways.

1237
01:29:16,451 --> 01:29:21,542
There's nothing wrong
with holding each other. Hmm?

1238
01:29:21,618 --> 01:29:24,106
Nothing at all.

1239
01:29:24,184 --> 01:29:26,116
And sleeping with each other.

1240
01:29:26,184 --> 01:29:28,116
We can do that.

1241
01:29:28,183 --> 01:29:30,945
And... loving each other forever.

1242
01:29:32,484 --> 01:29:35,574
What did I ever do to deserve you?

1243
01:29:35,650 --> 01:29:39,912
Usually that line is screamed at me
by somebody running out the door...

1244
01:29:39,984 --> 01:29:43,746
not standing in front
of me and staying.

1245
01:29:43,817 --> 01:29:46,579
It makes for a nice change.

1246
01:30:07,683 --> 01:30:09,615
Ah, flowers.

1247
01:30:09,683 --> 01:30:12,513
How thoughtful.

1248
01:30:12,583 --> 01:30:15,673
Whoo. We like the same merlot.

1249
01:30:15,750 --> 01:30:18,682
It's actually the very same bottle
that you brought to my house.

1250
01:30:18,750 --> 01:30:21,238
Excellent.

1251
01:30:21,316 --> 01:30:23,339
Come on in.

1252
01:30:23,417 --> 01:30:25,349
Wow.

1253
01:30:30,583 --> 01:30:34,174
- You're wondering where dinner is.
- Uh, I must say.

1254
01:30:34,250 --> 01:30:36,511
I have a little confession to make.

1255
01:30:36,583 --> 01:30:39,844
I invited you to dinner at my house,
but I can't cook.

1256
01:30:39,917 --> 01:30:42,008
Oh.

1257
01:30:42,083 --> 01:30:44,016
I can order delivery.

1258
01:30:44,084 --> 01:30:46,174
All right.

1259
01:30:46,250 --> 01:30:48,511
Chinese food is my specialty.

1260
01:30:58,183 --> 01:31:00,614
What are we making?

1261
01:31:00,683 --> 01:31:02,774
Some hemlock.

1262
01:31:02,849 --> 01:31:05,372
Oh, please, don't deprive
the kids of their mother.

1263
01:31:05,450 --> 01:31:09,779
- Oh, I'm not making it for me.
- Ah, that's the Hannah that I know.

1264
01:31:09,850 --> 01:31:13,713
Well, you seem to know me
a lot better than I know you.

1265
01:31:13,783 --> 01:31:16,113
You know that's not true.

1266
01:31:16,183 --> 01:31:21,479
Do you remember what you told
the kids about falling in love?

1267
01:31:22,849 --> 01:31:25,281
- No.
- Well, I do.

1268
01:31:25,350 --> 01:31:28,782
You said that the wonderful thing
about falling in love...

1269
01:31:28,849 --> 01:31:34,611
is that you learn everything
about that person, and so quickly.

1270
01:31:34,682 --> 01:31:36,614
And if it's true love...

1271
01:31:36,682 --> 01:31:40,114
then you start to see yourself
through their eyes...

1272
01:31:40,182 --> 01:31:42,115
and it brings out
the best in you...

1273
01:31:42,182 --> 01:31:46,615
and it's almost as if you're
falling in love with yourself.

1274
01:31:46,682 --> 01:31:49,944
- I said that?
- Mm-hmm.

1275
01:31:50,016 --> 01:31:54,311
Well, 25 years ago,
I needed to feel that again.

1276
01:31:54,383 --> 01:31:57,712
Feel that I was worth loving.

1277
01:31:57,783 --> 01:32:00,215
Because somehow I knew...

1278
01:32:00,283 --> 01:32:04,612
that would be my last time
to have that particular feeling.

1279
01:32:06,449 --> 01:32:10,040
- You couldn't have it with me?
- Oh, I did have it with you...

1280
01:32:10,115 --> 01:32:12,206
but I'd forgotten it.

1281
01:32:12,282 --> 01:32:15,043
I hadn't forgotten
why I loved you...

1282
01:32:15,115 --> 01:32:17,945
but I'd forgotten
why you loved me.

1283
01:32:21,949 --> 01:32:24,709
And Wendy made me remember...

1284
01:32:24,783 --> 01:32:28,374
that I was a pretty terrific fellow.

1285
01:32:28,448 --> 01:32:30,880
Bully for Wendy.

1286
01:32:30,948 --> 01:32:34,880
But I knew that
I couldn't sleep with her.

1287
01:32:34,948 --> 01:32:36,574
Why?

1288
01:32:36,648 --> 01:32:40,808
Because I would have left you...
and the kids.

1289
01:32:51,449 --> 01:32:54,312
What are we thinking?

1290
01:32:54,382 --> 01:32:56,973
Hot liquid and facial burns.

1291
01:32:57,048 --> 01:32:59,309
Oh.

1292
01:32:59,382 --> 01:33:04,474
Remember the day
Wendy left the company...

1293
01:33:04,548 --> 01:33:07,480
- and went to Seattle?
- Yes.

1294
01:33:07,548 --> 01:33:09,639
I thought for a while
you might go with her.

1295
01:33:09,715 --> 01:33:12,647
Me too, but I didn't.

1296
01:33:16,381 --> 01:33:18,973
When I came home that day...

1297
01:33:19,048 --> 01:33:23,140
I realized that I was
more in love with you...

1298
01:33:23,215 --> 01:33:25,476
than ever before.

1299
01:33:27,214 --> 01:33:30,647
How did that thunderbolt strike you?

1300
01:33:30,715 --> 01:33:33,805
Because I'd made a choice.

1301
01:33:35,047 --> 01:33:38,481
I took one look at you...

1302
01:33:38,548 --> 01:33:43,140
and I knew I'd made
the right choice.

1303
01:33:43,214 --> 01:33:45,476
I know that sounds daft...

1304
01:33:45,547 --> 01:33:49,311
but my love for somebody else...

1305
01:33:49,381 --> 01:33:52,246
made me love you more...

1306
01:33:52,314 --> 01:33:56,576
because I sought...

1307
01:33:56,648 --> 01:33:58,580
to reclaim myself.

1308
01:34:00,314 --> 01:34:02,575
And, Hannah...

1309
01:34:02,648 --> 01:34:05,580
you're still the right choice.

1310
01:34:08,648 --> 01:34:11,580
We made a child that day.

1311
01:34:11,647 --> 01:34:13,580
We did, indeed.

1312
01:34:13,648 --> 01:34:16,239
Our Jo-Jo.

1313
01:34:16,313 --> 01:34:19,905
Yeah. We did, indeed.

1314
01:34:35,314 --> 01:34:37,905
- Cheers.
- Thank you.

1315
01:34:40,647 --> 01:34:43,579
Trent...

1316
01:34:43,647 --> 01:34:45,704
I have to tell you something.

1317
01:34:45,781 --> 01:34:49,235
Oh, this doesn't begin with
"Trent, you are a nice guy," does it?

1318
01:34:49,314 --> 01:34:51,609
- No.
- Whew.

1319
01:34:51,680 --> 01:34:55,339
The problem I have with you--

1320
01:34:56,746 --> 01:34:59,009
We have problems?

1321
01:35:02,913 --> 01:35:06,676
The problem I have with you...

1322
01:35:06,746 --> 01:35:09,508
is that I'm attracted to you.

1323
01:35:11,580 --> 01:35:13,546
And that's a problem?

1324
01:35:15,614 --> 01:35:18,738
It is for me.

1325
01:35:18,813 --> 01:35:22,007
It's, um--

1326
01:35:23,247 --> 01:35:25,338
Gosh, this is so embarrassing.

1327
01:35:25,414 --> 01:35:27,346
What?

1328
01:35:27,414 --> 01:35:30,005
Don't be embarrassed.

1329
01:35:33,746 --> 01:35:36,838
I don't deal with passion well.

1330
01:35:36,913 --> 01:35:40,004
Maybe you don't like
that loss of control.

1331
01:35:40,081 --> 01:35:44,172
You prefer to be the director,
telling everyone what to do.

1332
01:35:45,746 --> 01:35:48,337
It's pretty painfully obvious,
isn't it?

1333
01:35:48,414 --> 01:35:51,607
Somewhat painful, yes.

1334
01:35:54,180 --> 01:35:57,441
You know, there's something
you'll find out about me.

1335
01:35:57,513 --> 01:35:59,945
What's that?

1336
01:36:03,679 --> 01:36:06,441
That I take direction pretty well.

1337
01:36:31,846 --> 01:36:33,778
- Trent.
- Yeah?

1338
01:36:33,846 --> 01:36:36,437
You're gonna think what I'm about
to say is really ridiculous.

1339
01:36:36,513 --> 01:36:39,275
You're worried about Barley,
and you want to go back to your place.

1340
01:36:39,346 --> 01:36:43,278
Oh, my God.
This is way fucking spooky.

1341
01:36:56,280 --> 01:36:59,212
I forgot what it felt like
to be this close to someone.

1342
01:36:59,279 --> 01:37:03,711
I have never been
this close to anyone.

1343
01:37:11,112 --> 01:37:14,374
We're always gonna be honest
with each other, right?

1344
01:37:14,446 --> 01:37:16,877
It's essential.

1345
01:37:16,945 --> 01:37:21,877
Um... I have
to confess something.

1346
01:37:23,079 --> 01:37:25,012
Shoot.

1347
01:37:27,112 --> 01:37:31,806
Um... the night we went to the movies,
and you walked me to my car--

1348
01:37:31,879 --> 01:37:34,209
You mean the car
that you pretended was stolen?

1349
01:37:34,279 --> 01:37:37,609
You knew?

1350
01:37:37,678 --> 01:37:39,974
Joan--

1351
01:37:43,612 --> 01:37:46,044
I may have been
a basket case that evening...

1352
01:37:46,112 --> 01:37:48,703
but I wasn't born yesterday.

1353
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:50,870
I am so embarrassed.

1354
01:37:52,378 --> 01:37:55,640
No. No.

1355
01:37:58,211 --> 01:38:01,905
Oh-- Oh, well.

1356
01:38:05,879 --> 01:38:07,936
I so very much love you.

1357
01:38:08,012 --> 01:38:10,637
And I love you.

1358
01:38:12,545 --> 01:38:14,477
And, Joan?

1359
01:38:14,546 --> 01:38:16,477
Yes, Keenan.

1360
01:38:16,545 --> 01:38:21,170
In time... I may even get
to like this mangy cat of ours.

1361
01:38:23,545 --> 01:38:26,773
She's got her eye on you.

1362
01:38:28,677 --> 01:38:30,644
And that's her good one?

1363
01:38:54,545 --> 01:38:56,636
I think this is gonna work.

1364
01:38:56,712 --> 01:38:58,643
Yeah?
Why is that?

1365
01:38:58,712 --> 01:39:01,143
- Because on an intimacy scale...
- Mm-hmm.

1366
01:39:01,211 --> 01:39:03,302
having somebody watch me
brush my teeth...

1367
01:39:03,378 --> 01:39:05,969
is right up there with seeing me
on a Sazerac swing...

1368
01:39:06,044 --> 01:39:08,135
and I'm not minding it.

1369
01:39:20,044 --> 01:39:22,942
Hmm?

1370
01:39:27,545 --> 01:39:30,477
This had better be good.

1371
01:39:30,544 --> 01:39:32,477
Oh--

1372
01:39:39,377 --> 01:39:43,310
Uh... I'll catch
the first flight out.

1373
01:40:08,310 --> 01:40:10,242
Mildred.

1374
01:40:29,310 --> 01:40:33,571
You don't know what it means to me,
for you to be here.

1375
01:40:38,310 --> 01:40:40,742
He was my first love.

1376
01:40:43,010 --> 01:40:44,943
And my last.

1377
01:40:45,010 --> 01:40:48,704
Next to Jack.

1378
01:40:48,777 --> 01:40:50,744
Did you know him?
Jack?

1379
01:40:53,743 --> 01:40:55,767
He was good for Mark.

1380
01:40:55,843 --> 01:41:00,173
Well, I would have liked
to have known him.

1381
01:41:02,743 --> 01:41:06,176
I guess you all thought
I couldn't handle it.

1382
01:41:09,877 --> 01:41:12,843
Until just a week ago...

1383
01:41:12,910 --> 01:41:16,933
I still harbored the fantasy that
you and he would get together again.

1384
01:41:20,476 --> 01:41:23,670
We had some nice talks
before he died.

1385
01:41:24,910 --> 01:41:27,467
I'm glad we had those talks.

1386
01:41:27,543 --> 01:41:32,168
I felt like his mother again.

1387
01:41:42,410 --> 01:41:45,672
I'll never know
everything about Mark...

1388
01:41:47,576 --> 01:41:51,030
but I know some things about him now
that I never knew before.

1389
01:41:51,110 --> 01:41:55,939
I don't think we need to know everything
about the people we love.

1390
01:42:08,710 --> 01:42:12,039
Yeah. Hello?

1391
01:42:12,109 --> 01:42:14,268
- Trent?
- Hey.

1392
01:42:14,342 --> 01:42:16,275
How are you?

1393
01:42:16,343 --> 01:42:18,275
I'm good.

1394
01:42:18,343 --> 01:42:20,775
I was, uh-- I was just calling in
for my messages.

1395
01:42:20,842 --> 01:42:22,775
What are you doing there?

1396
01:42:22,842 --> 01:42:25,104
Oh, l, uh--

1397
01:42:25,176 --> 01:42:27,266
I took Barley over to my house...

1398
01:42:27,343 --> 01:42:30,104
and I don't think he liked it.

1399
01:42:30,175 --> 01:42:32,869
Actually, I'm sure he didn't like it.
He peed all over my stuff.

1400
01:42:32,942 --> 01:42:37,271
So... I came back here.

1401
01:42:37,343 --> 01:42:39,604
I'm glad.

1402
01:42:40,676 --> 01:42:42,937
How was everything where you are?

1403
01:42:43,009 --> 01:42:46,600
In its own way,
it was quite beautiful.

1404
01:42:48,176 --> 01:42:51,199
- Trent?
- Yeah?

1405
01:42:53,442 --> 01:42:55,908
Is it too late to say,
"l love you"?

1406
01:42:55,975 --> 01:42:57,965
It's early.

1407
01:43:06,443 --> 01:43:08,374
She's coming back tomorrow.

1408
01:43:12,609 --> 01:43:17,338
And then sleeping arrangements
will definitely be revised.

1409
01:43:30,941 --> 01:43:32,930
Come over later.

1410
01:43:34,108 --> 01:43:36,870
I don't--
I don't know if I'm up to it.

1411
01:43:36,942 --> 01:43:38,931
Well, think about it, Mildred.

1412
01:43:39,009 --> 01:43:41,270
I'd love to have you there.

1413
01:43:41,342 --> 01:43:43,274
I'll think about it.

1414
01:44:21,608 --> 01:44:23,541
Mom?

1415
01:44:27,041 --> 01:44:30,370
- Mom?
- Yes, out here, Meredith.

1416
01:44:31,541 --> 01:44:33,632
Make three--

1417
01:44:33,708 --> 01:44:36,299
Three times as many seems reasonable.

1418
01:44:36,375 --> 01:44:39,135
- Hello, sweetheart.
- Hi. Hi.

1419
01:44:39,207 --> 01:44:43,231
That sister of yours was
supposed to be here an hour ago
to help me with all this.

1420
01:44:43,307 --> 01:44:47,297
And here she is,
looking fabulous I might add.

1421
01:44:47,374 --> 01:44:50,136
I'm so sorry I'm late.
What can I do?

1422
01:44:50,208 --> 01:44:54,401
You can put on a bra,
and then you can do everything else.

1423
01:44:54,474 --> 01:44:56,407
Oh, it's not like
you were any help.

1424
01:44:56,474 --> 01:44:58,406
- Why, you know my play was opening.
- I know.

1425
01:44:58,474 --> 01:45:01,907
That's right. Your father has the review
on the refrigerator already.

1426
01:45:01,975 --> 01:45:04,566
Mr. Crabby from the Times
gave it a rave. Congrats.

1427
01:45:04,640 --> 01:45:07,572
- You mean you read it?
- I'm proud of my younger sister.

1428
01:45:07,641 --> 01:45:11,403
Now to work. Believe it or not,
I have worn these fingers to a frazzle.

1429
01:45:11,474 --> 01:45:14,736
Speed dialing is so strenuous.
I've taken care of the caterers...

1430
01:45:14,808 --> 01:45:18,240
the flowers are being arranged
as we speak, and I've hired a minister.

1431
01:45:18,307 --> 01:45:21,704
You did tell him to go easy
on the God stuff, hmm?

1432
01:45:21,775 --> 01:45:23,740
Yes, Daddy.

1433
01:45:23,807 --> 01:45:26,399
Gracie, Gracie, Gracie.

1434
01:45:26,474 --> 01:45:29,065
The other bearded one
will barely get a mention.

1435
01:45:29,141 --> 01:45:31,073
All right.

1436
01:45:31,141 --> 01:45:33,402
Ah, my Meredith.

1437
01:45:36,341 --> 01:45:38,204
You know, we do have to change.

1438
01:45:38,274 --> 01:45:41,569
Well, if I have to wear a tux,
she has to wear a bra.

1439
01:45:41,640 --> 01:45:43,607
Inside.

1440
01:45:43,673 --> 01:45:46,196
- I never knew what happiness was
until I married your mother...
- Just march.

1441
01:45:46,273 --> 01:45:48,399
and by then it was too late.

1442
01:45:48,474 --> 01:45:50,405
You are so--

1443
01:45:50,473 --> 01:45:53,735
Now, listen. I put you in a seat
next to Hugh and me because I figured...

1444
01:45:53,807 --> 01:45:55,739
you might be coming alone and--

1445
01:45:55,807 --> 01:45:59,331
Yeah, well, you might have to do
some rearranging because, um...

1446
01:45:59,408 --> 01:46:02,134
because I have a date.

1447
01:46:02,207 --> 01:46:04,036
We'll change fast.

1448
01:46:04,107 --> 01:46:07,402
You know
you're gonna tell me every single thing.

1449
01:46:12,673 --> 01:46:14,605
Mom, Dad...

1450
01:46:14,674 --> 01:46:16,435
this is Trent.

1451
01:46:16,507 --> 01:46:18,440
- Hi.
- It's a pleasure, Trent.

1452
01:46:18,507 --> 01:46:20,439
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
Congratulations.
- Hello.

1453
01:46:20,508 --> 01:46:23,667
- Thank you.
- Hi. I'm the older married sister.

1454
01:46:23,740 --> 01:46:26,729
- Hi.
- Sorry. Gracie.

1455
01:46:26,807 --> 01:46:28,636
I see what you mean.
Okay, we better get started.

1456
01:46:28,707 --> 01:46:32,140
- We're 20 minutes behind
and the minister has another service.
- We can't go without Jo-Jo.

1457
01:46:32,207 --> 01:46:35,229
- Moi.
- Oh! Now we can.

1458
01:46:35,306 --> 01:46:37,239
- Hi, sweetheart.
- Mom, you look beautiful.

1459
01:46:37,306 --> 01:46:39,829
- Thank you.
You're forgiven for being late.
- Thank you.

1460
01:46:39,906 --> 01:46:42,668
Dad, wow.

1461
01:46:42,740 --> 01:46:45,501
Forty years ago,
he wore jeans to our wedding.

1462
01:46:45,573 --> 01:46:47,505
You should have heard the fuss
he made this time...

1463
01:46:47,573 --> 01:46:49,505
when he found out
he had to wear a tux.

1464
01:46:49,572 --> 01:46:51,936
What an anger ball.

1465
01:46:52,006 --> 01:46:54,029
Oh, Mom, Dad, everybody...

1466
01:46:54,106 --> 01:46:56,800
- this is Keenan.
- How do you do, Keenan?

1467
01:46:56,874 --> 01:46:59,806
- Very good, sir.
- Good to meet you, Keenan.

1468
01:46:59,873 --> 01:47:02,931
- Nice to meet you.
- Champagne. Jo-Jo?

1469
01:47:03,007 --> 01:47:06,097
- Um... I'm okay.
- Oh.

1470
01:47:06,173 --> 01:47:09,105
Keenan and I are just gonna
have a couple Cokes or something.

1471
01:47:09,173 --> 01:47:13,435
Keenan, did I tell you
how very good it is to meet you?

1472
01:47:13,507 --> 01:47:16,268
Funny.

1473
01:47:21,670 --> 01:47:24,157
Hannah and Paul have asked
their family and friends...

1474
01:47:24,237 --> 01:47:27,669
to join them here today
in their home...

1475
01:47:27,736 --> 01:47:29,929
to reaffirm their wedding vows...

1476
01:47:30,004 --> 01:47:32,730
40 years since the first time.

1477
01:47:36,136 --> 01:47:38,159
What's this?
No applause?

1478
01:47:38,236 --> 01:47:42,931
Don't they realize what a miracle
40 years of marriage is?

1479
01:47:43,003 --> 01:47:46,196
Probably not, but I do.

1480
01:47:49,337 --> 01:47:51,564
Hannah and Paul,
you come here today...

1481
01:47:51,636 --> 01:47:55,069
to repledge your love,
your undying love.

1482
01:47:55,136 --> 01:47:57,567
A love that has lasted many years...

1483
01:47:57,636 --> 01:48:02,228
and will go on lasting, I'm certain,
many years more.

1484
01:48:02,302 --> 01:48:05,064
You stand here today
before God...

1485
01:48:05,136 --> 01:48:08,260
your family and friends
to celebrate...

1486
01:48:08,337 --> 01:48:11,359
to reaffirm your lasting love
for each other.

1487
01:48:11,436 --> 01:48:15,198
Hannah and Paul have asked
to keep the ceremony simple...

1488
01:48:15,269 --> 01:48:18,497
and to that end they each set
a challenge for the other:

1489
01:48:18,569 --> 01:48:23,025
to find a sentence that best describes
their feelings for the other.

1490
01:48:23,102 --> 01:48:25,761
Hannah? Paul?

1491
01:48:29,603 --> 01:48:32,967
You are the tenant of my heart...

1492
01:48:33,035 --> 01:48:36,433
often behind in the rent...

1493
01:48:36,502 --> 01:48:39,764
but impossible to evict.

1494
01:48:39,835 --> 01:48:42,858
If I had to do it all over again...

1495
01:48:42,936 --> 01:48:47,731
I wouldn't do it...
any different.

1496
01:49:30,668 --> 01:49:33,429
Mildred, I'm so sorry.

1497
01:49:45,168 --> 01:49:48,294
- So, that's who I stole
your V.W. for, huh?
- Yeah.

1498
01:49:48,368 --> 01:49:51,562
Thank you.

1499
01:49:54,235 --> 01:49:57,690
- And you thought
it wasn't gonna work out.
- Yeah.

1500
01:50:02,102 --> 01:50:04,499
That was really...
beautiful.

1501
01:50:05,902 --> 01:50:07,834
It was.

1502
01:50:09,368 --> 01:50:11,300
Yes, it was.

1503
01:50:16,001 --> 01:50:20,127
Think we'll be having
a fortieth wedding ceremony?

1504
01:50:24,069 --> 01:50:26,694
I don't know, Hugh.

1505
01:50:44,035 --> 01:50:45,966
Would you like to think so?

1506
01:50:48,567 --> 01:50:50,624
I don't know, Hugh.

1507
01:50:53,368 --> 01:50:55,526
- Hey.
- Hello.

1508
01:50:55,601 --> 01:50:58,033
Hi.

1509
01:50:58,101 --> 01:51:01,965
- How did you like that improv class?
- That was... interesting.

1510
01:51:02,034 --> 01:51:04,795
I think it's so cool to pretend to be
somebody else every night for a week.

1511
01:51:04,868 --> 01:51:06,800
I took it twice.

1512
01:51:08,235 --> 01:51:10,166
This is Keenan, by the way.

1513
01:51:10,234 --> 01:51:12,860
Hi. Hugh.
I'm, uh, married to Gracie here.

1514
01:51:12,934 --> 01:51:14,627
Hugh designs video games.

1515
01:51:14,701 --> 01:51:19,191
- Any I'd know?
- Um, "Killer Golf." That was the last.

1516
01:51:19,267 --> 01:51:21,131
Oh, man, that game was awesome.

1517
01:51:21,201 --> 01:51:23,894
You have a hell of an imagination.

1518
01:51:23,967 --> 01:51:26,593
Hey, you owe me a dance.

1519
01:51:26,667 --> 01:51:29,156
- Just one?
- No.

1520
01:51:38,566 --> 01:51:40,499
Gracie...

1521
01:51:42,467 --> 01:51:44,399
would you like to dance?

1522
01:51:44,467 --> 01:51:48,365
Yes. Yes, I would.

1523
01:51:55,600 --> 01:51:59,726
You know, I can't think
of a better way to meet your family.

1524
01:51:59,800 --> 01:52:02,358
Other than maybe dropping a bookshelf
on their heads.

1525
01:52:07,299 --> 01:52:09,459
They look so perfect together.

1526
01:52:11,534 --> 01:52:14,056
They look so perfect together.

1527
01:52:14,133 --> 01:52:16,099
Just like we do.

1528
01:52:16,167 --> 01:52:19,224
Ow!

1529
01:52:19,299 --> 01:52:24,322
Sorry. Now you know the real reason
why I like to dance alone.

1530
01:52:24,400 --> 01:52:28,832
It's okay.
You can step on my feet anytime.

1531
01:52:28,900 --> 01:52:32,458
Just, you know, next time I'll wear
some steel-toed shoes or something.

1532
01:52:57,033 --> 01:52:59,464
What are we thinking?

1533
01:52:59,533 --> 01:53:02,329
If only they knew
what we know.

1534
01:53:02,399 --> 01:53:05,922
Then it would be all too easy.

1535
01:53:05,999 --> 01:53:08,693
- The trumpet player--
- Hmm?

1536
01:53:08,766 --> 01:53:11,062
- Your friend?
- Yeah.

1537
01:53:11,133 --> 01:53:14,587
The one who said talking about love
is like dancing about architecture.

1538
01:53:14,666 --> 01:53:16,598
Mm-hmm.

1539
01:53:17,833 --> 01:53:21,196
Well, what do you say
we prove him wrong?

1540
01:53:27,000 --> 01:53:29,591
I think we already have.

